DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum M Protein Outcome Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date related to the results of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood serum, the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed, for monoclonal immunoglobulin, a protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains that is found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma; the protein is not produced in response to an antigen, but it is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum M Protein Outcome
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the results of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood serum, the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed, for monoclonal immunoglobulin, a protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains that is found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma; the protein is not produced in response to an antigen, but it is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: The clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed.:A protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains. Monoclonal immunoglobulin (M protein) is found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma. The protein is not produced in response to an antigen, but it is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: The clear portion of the blood that remains after the removal of the blood cells and the clotting proteins.

A protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains. Monoclonal immunoglobulin (M protein) is found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma. The protein is not produced in response to an antigen, but it is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The date on which an observation was made or an event occurred.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: a particular day specified as the time something has, or will, happen.

Concepts.definition: The particular day, month and year an event has happened or will happen.
